      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MYSTA MOON WALKER (1) has been racing very well from some tough barriers at Gloucester Park. Recorded back-to-back placings then did a fine job last time out when successful by 2 metres after racing wide. Has the benefit of the inside draw this time and won over this distance the only time he raced here. INTO THE FUTURE (2) galloped from the standing start last time but was good when he came from the back row for second at Gloucester Park prior. Has the benefit of a good draw and is suited back behind a mobile. CONTROL THE ROOM (10) drew wide when resuming at Gloucester Park four days ago. Tricky barrier again but goes well at this circuit and distance with two wins and placing from three attempts. GOGGINS (3) missed by a nose when second at Gloucester Park last start and draws lower.",
